51:09.000 --> 51:12.000
Can you sing the British National Anthem, please?

51:12.000 --> 51:15.000
I don't think that's a very good question, Alba.

51:15.000 --> 51:17.000
Oh, it's a lovely question.

51:17.000 --> 51:19.000
I can sing it.

51:19.000 --> 51:23.000
God save our gracious queen.

51:23.000 --> 51:26.000
No, please, no, please.

51:26.000 --> 51:29.000
God save the queen.

51:29.000 --> 51:31.000
Tell your mother to shut up, please.

51:31.000 --> 51:33.000
Nothing glorious.

51:33.000 --> 51:34.000
Happy.

51:34.000 --> 51:35.000
Alba.

51:35.000 --> 51:36.000
Let me know.

51:36.000 --> 51:37.000
No, the two.

51:37.000 --> 51:38.000
Mother.

51:38.000 --> 51:40.000
Oh, for us.

51:40.000 --> 51:42.000
Everyone joining.

51:42.000 --> 51:46.000
God save the queen.

51:46.000 --> 51:49.000
Wonderful, wonderful.

51:49.000 --> 51:51.000
Thank you very much.

51:54.000 --> 51:56.000
Row, row, row the boat.

52:02.000 --> 52:06.000
You were certainly a hit at the school, Mum.

52:06.000 --> 52:09.000
I think the word is twit, not hit.

52:09.000 --> 52:11.000
What did he say?

52:11.000 --> 52:14.000
You know I can't hear very well.

52:14.000 --> 52:15.000
Nothing, Mum.

52:15.000 --> 52:18.000
Anyway, what a wonderful view.

52:18.000 --> 52:20.000
It's a lovely place.

52:20.000 --> 52:24.000
It's lovely and peaceful with the mountains in the background.

52:24.000 --> 52:26.000
Where are we?

52:26.000 --> 52:28.000
Keem sea.

52:28.000 --> 52:30.000
It's a lake.

52:30.000 --> 52:33.000
Dead lakes said something about it being a sea.

52:33.000 --> 52:35.000
His geography is a bit wrong.

52:35.000 --> 52:37.000
This isn't a sea, it's a lake.

52:37.000 --> 52:39.000
Don't they teach them anything at school?

52:39.000 --> 52:40.000
No, Dad.

52:40.000 --> 52:42.000
The German word for a lake is sea.

52:42.000 --> 52:44.000
But why?

52:44.000 --> 52:46.000
Why call a lake a sea?

52:46.000 --> 52:48.000
I don't understand the cracks.

52:48.000 --> 52:50.000
Don't be so rude, Pete.

52:50.000 --> 52:53.000
They are so strange.

52:53.000 --> 52:57.000
Do you want to know what happened when I went for a walk with Boris this morning?

52:57.000 --> 53:00.000
No, but I think you're going to tell us.

53:00.000 --> 53:05.000
An old German fossil started shouting at me in German and waving a stick at me.

53:05.000 --> 53:08.000
What were you doing, trying to chat her up?

53:08.000 --> 53:09.000
Of course not.

53:09.000 --> 53:12.000
She was older than your mother, if that's possible.

53:12.000 --> 53:14.000
I'm not so old, Pete.

53:14.000 --> 53:18.000
The old deer was waiting at the traffic lights on the opposite side.

53:18.000 --> 53:20.000
I don't know why she was waiting.

53:20.000 --> 53:22.000
There were no cars coming.

53:22.000 --> 53:24.000
So, I crossed over the street.

53:24.000 --> 53:28.000
As I got to the other side, she started screaming and waving her stick.

53:28.000 --> 53:30.000
I don't see what's so funny.

53:30.000 --> 53:35.000
I thought maybe she's escaped from the loony bit, or maybe drank too much snaps.

53:35.000 --> 53:40.000
In Germany, it is normal to wait at the traffic lights until the light turns green.

53:40.000 --> 53:43.000
Yes, but there weren't any cars.

53:43.000 --> 53:45.000
That doesn't matter, it's the law.

53:45.000 --> 53:47.000
Typical Germans.

53:47.000 --> 53:49.000
What a stupid law.

53:49.000 --> 53:52.000
Oh, look, rowing boats.

53:52.000 --> 53:54.000
I want to go on the lake.

53:54.000 --> 53:55.000
Come on, everyone.

53:55.000 --> 53:57.000
We can eat afterwards.

53:57.000 --> 53:59.000
That's a good idea.

53:59.000 --> 54:00.000
Let's go.

54:00.000 --> 54:01.000
All right.

54:01.000 --> 54:02.000
You too, Pete.

54:02.000 --> 54:06.000
Good and talk.

54:06.000 --> 54:09.000
Viervant ein rowing shift.

54:09.000 --> 54:11.000
For ein our bitter.

54:11.000 --> 54:12.000
Danke.

54:12.000 --> 54:15.000
Your German is so good, Josie.

54:15.000 --> 54:17.000
It's wonderful you're with us.

54:17.000 --> 54:19.000
I don't know what we would have done without you.

54:19.000 --> 54:21.000
Stayed in England.

54:21.000 --> 54:23.000
It's important to meet other people.

54:23.000 --> 54:25.000
Get to know how they lived at.

54:25.000 --> 54:27.000
I don't see why.

54:27.000 --> 54:31.000
There's no better holiday than a week or two in Blackpool.

54:31.000 --> 54:33.000
It has everything you need.

54:33.000 --> 54:34.000
Except sun.

54:34.000 --> 54:36.000
The sun comes out on Sundays.

54:36.000 --> 54:40.000
Not when we're there, and we're there every year.

54:40.000 --> 54:42.000
Oh, I like it.

54:42.000 --> 54:43.000
Here we are.

54:43.000 --> 54:45.000
I want to roll.

54:45.000 --> 54:46.000
I want to roll.

54:46.000 --> 54:47.000
I want to roll.

54:47.000 --> 54:48.000
Not so fast, Mum.

54:48.000 --> 54:49.000
Don't rock the boat.

54:49.000 --> 54:50.000
Oh, oh, oh.

54:50.000 --> 54:51.000
This is fun.

54:51.000 --> 54:53.000
I want to give everyone just sit down.

54:53.000 --> 54:55.000
Boris, lie down.

54:55.000 --> 54:59.000
Could you tell your mum that if she wants to roll, she needs to turn around.

54:59.000 --> 55:01.000
I don't know what you mean.

55:01.000 --> 55:03.000
Oh, absolutely.

55:03.000 --> 55:05.000
We're going backwards.

55:05.000 --> 55:06.000
Be careful, Mum.

55:06.000 --> 55:08.000
Oh, oh.

55:08.000 --> 55:09.000
Careful.

55:09.000 --> 55:11.000
Oh, this is fun.

55:11.000 --> 55:13.000
Don't rock the boat, Josie.

55:13.000 --> 55:15.000
Give the oars to me.

55:15.000 --> 55:17.000
You have no idea.

55:17.000 --> 55:19.000
No, I want to roll.

55:19.000 --> 55:20.000
I want them.

55:20.000 --> 55:22.000
You are a danger to civilisation.

55:22.000 --> 55:24.000
Stop eating the two of you.

55:24.000 --> 55:26.000
You're behaving just like children.

55:26.000 --> 55:27.000
I want them.

55:27.000 --> 55:28.000
Give them to me.

55:28.000 --> 55:30.000
I've had enough.

55:30.000 --> 55:32.000
Can we go back to the shore now?

55:34.000 --> 55:36.000
I don't believe it.

55:36.000 --> 55:38.000
What a holiday.

55:38.000 --> 55:39.000
Your mother started it.

55:39.000 --> 55:40.000
No, I did.

55:40.000 --> 55:41.000
Both of you.

55:42.000 --> 55:44.000
Now, let me get out of this boat.

55:44.000 --> 55:45.000
Be careful.

55:45.000 --> 55:46.000
Don't do that.

55:46.000 --> 55:47.000
No, the other way.

55:47.000 --> 55:49.000
Put one foot on the bank.

55:49.000 --> 55:50.000
No, don't grab.

55:50.000 --> 55:51.000
Throw the other way.

55:51.000 --> 55:53.000
Wait, which way?

55:53.000 --> 55:54.000
I'm confused.

55:54.000 --> 55:55.000
Give them to me.

55:55.000 --> 55:57.000
You silly old bat.

55:57.000 --> 55:58.000
No.

55:58.000 --> 55:59.000
Oh.

56:02.000 --> 56:03.000
Help me.

56:03.000 --> 56:04.000
I'm drowning.

56:08.000 --> 56:09.000
