59:17.000 --> 59:19.000
It's a long journey to the ferry port.

59:19.000 --> 59:20.000
But...

59:20.000 --> 59:22.000
Oh, alright.

59:22.000 --> 59:24.000
I get the message.

59:24.000 --> 59:25.000
Right.

59:25.000 --> 59:26.000
Okay.

59:26.000 --> 59:29.000
I'm driving home on my own with Boris.

59:29.000 --> 59:30.000
Super.

59:30.000 --> 59:31.000
Super.

59:31.000 --> 59:32.000
So epic.

59:37.000 --> 59:39.000
Pete's trip home.

59:49.000 --> 59:50.000
Now, dear.

59:50.000 --> 59:52.000
Are you sure you have everything?

59:52.000 --> 59:53.000
Yes, dear.

59:53.000 --> 59:55.000
I packed the car myself.

59:55.000 --> 59:57.000
That's what I mean.

59:57.000 --> 59:59.000
Do you want me to check it for you?

59:59.000 --> 01:00:01.000
I'm not totally useless.

01:00:01.000 --> 01:00:02.000
No, dear.

01:00:02.000 --> 01:00:03.000
Of course you're not.

01:00:03.000 --> 01:00:05.000
Hope the three of, er...

01:00:05.000 --> 01:00:10.000
Two of you have a nice journey, Dad.

01:00:10.000 --> 01:00:12.000
What?

01:00:12.000 --> 01:00:13.000
Three.

01:00:13.000 --> 01:00:15.000
What are you talking about, Josie?

01:00:15.000 --> 01:00:17.000
There's only me and Boris alone.

01:00:17.000 --> 01:00:18.000
Er...

01:00:18.000 --> 01:00:19.000
Yes, Dad.

01:00:19.000 --> 01:00:20.000
I, er...

01:00:20.000 --> 01:00:21.000
Forgot.

01:00:21.000 --> 01:00:22.000
Forgot?

01:00:22.000 --> 01:00:23.000
What, our family?

01:00:23.000 --> 01:00:24.000
Er, right.

01:00:24.000 --> 01:00:25.000
Goodbye.

01:00:25.000 --> 01:00:27.000
Have a nice week.

01:00:27.000 --> 01:00:29.000
Phone me if you have time.

01:00:29.000 --> 01:00:30.000
Bye.

01:00:35.000 --> 01:00:37.000
I hope he's alright by himself.

01:00:37.000 --> 01:00:40.000
He's happiest when he's with his car.

01:00:40.000 --> 01:00:42.000
Yes, but...

01:00:42.000 --> 01:00:44.000
